—
Some people have a gift
—
My incredible friend @thebeautyhaus is one of those people who instantly makes you feel at home. She shows up with her whole self, full radiant presence and listens with deep attention
—
I’m grateful for her friendship and so excited about the launch of her new hypnotherapy business
—
Hypnosis helped me at a critical time in my life. If you’re in a place where you could use some support, I invite you to connect with Shannon. She’s a true professional & a magical healer

node.text: You asked for help with calming down. This was the practice I shared with @ethanzohn on The Edge of Extinction to help us stay calm and patient in the midst of chaos and uncertainty. I hope you enjoy!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Parvati Shallow on June 15, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, child, people sitting and outdoors.

node.text:
Grief has different ways of getting your attention
—
My bike was stolen last week and I cried for 2 days straight. It wasn’t about the bike.
—
I’ve lost a lot in a very short period of time and I’m feeling it. Sometimes.
—
And, then sometimes I feel totally ok and able to do life perfectly fine
—
I’m sharing this in case any of you have lost something or someone you love and are feeling tender about it. You’re not alone in your emotional ups and downs
—
Don’t be afraid to open up and ask for help if you need it
—
I’m reaching out for more support than ever and getting lots of love in return. I’m still showing up for my clients and my family even through the emotional waves. I’m learning how to be grieving and be living at the same time
—
And if anyone has seen my bike out there in LA, call me! I want it back.
